OSOGBO – Governor Adegboyega Oyetola of Osun State has charged his predecessor in office, Rauf Aregbesola, and others appointed as Ministers to bring hard work and dedication to duty as Ministers of Federal Republic of Nigeria. Oyetola, in a congratulatory message in particular to Aregbesola, described his tenure as Governor gf Osun as one that would linger in the memories of the residents of the state for a very long time. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The congratulatory message issued and signed by his Chief Press Secretary, Ismail Omipidan, a copy of which was made available to newsmen, noted that Aregbesola’s achievements, especially in the area of good governance had been impactful on the lives of the people of the state. While congratulating on his inauguration as Minister of Federal Republic of Nigeria, Oyetola stressed that transformation of the state to the admiration of majority of the populace was a thing of joy and will not be forgotten for a very long time.